headline: New Transatlantic Routes Could Be a Game Changer for United Airlines (UAL)
summary: United Airlines recently announced its Summer 2026 schedule, unveiling new nonstop routes from Newark to four European cities, Split, Bari, Glasgow, and Santiago de Compostela, and introducing additional flights to Reykjavik, Seoul, and Tel Aviv, further expanding its international network. This expansion cements United’s position as the U.S. airline with the most transatlantic destinations and exclusive nonstop service to several key European cities.
